{% extends "base.html.twig" %}

{% block title %}About — NorthOps{% endblock %}
{% block description %}NorthOps is two senior engineers in Northern Ontario delivering fixed-price web apps, pipelines, DevOps, and AI engineering.{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
    <!-- About Text -->
    <section class="section section-hero">
        <div class="container container-narrow">
            <h1>About NorthOps</h1>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <div class="container container-narrow">
            <div class="text-block">
                <p>
                    NorthOps started because we kept seeing the same problem: companies that needed senior engineering
                    work done — a web app, a data pipeline, a deployment system — but couldn't justify a full-time hire
                    and didn't want to roll the dice on a freelancer or offshore team.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We're two senior engineers based in Northern Ontario. Between us we've built content platforms,
                    e-commerce systems, insurance tech, health data pipelines, and loyalty programs used by hundreds
                    of thousands of merchants. We've led teams, shipped production systems, and cleaned up the messes
                    left behind when projects go sideways.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We started NorthOps to offer something specific: senior-level engineering, fixed-price, delivered
                    in days. No account managers, no juniors, no layers of overhead. You talk to the engineers who
                    write the code. We scope tightly, build fast, and hand off clean.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We work from Northern Ontario — Sudbury and Noelville — because that's where we live. The geography
                    doesn't affect the quality of the work, but it does mean lower overhead, which we pass on as lower
                    prices. Our MVPs start at CAD $3,600 because we've built these systems enough times to know exactly
                    what's involved.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Team Bios -->
    <section class="section section-alt">
        <div class="container container-narrow">
            <h2>The team</h2>
            <div class="team-bios">
                <div class="team-bio">
                    <img src="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/499552?v=4" alt="Russell Jones" class="team-photo">
                    <h3>Russell Jones</h3>
                    <p class="team-title">Senior Engineer &amp; Co-Founder</p>
                    <p>
                        Russell is a senior full-stack developer with deep experience in content pipelines, automation
                        systems, and the Laravel/PHP ecosystem. He built North Cloud — a production content intelligence
                        platform that crawls, classifies, and routes news articles in real time.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Before NorthOps, Russell spent over a decade building web systems across agencies, startups,
                        and enterprise clients. He cares deeply about clean code, solid deployment pipelines, and
                        systems that the next person can actually understand and maintain.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        At NorthOps, Russell focuses on backend systems, data pipelines, deployment infrastructure,
                        and the CI/CD that keeps everything shipping reliably. Based in Sudbury, Ontario.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="team-bio">
                    <img src="/images/team/luc-hebert.jpg" alt="Luc Hebert" class="team-photo">
                    <h3>Luc Hebert</h3>
                    <p class="team-title">Senior Engineer &amp; Co-Founder</p>
                    <p>
                        Luc is a senior full-stack software engineer with experience spanning embedded systems,
                        LMS platforms, insurance tech, and health data systems. Most recently at Smile.io building
                        loyalty and e-commerce solutions for 100K+ Shopify merchants.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        From mining vehicle hardware in C to React and Ruby on Rails web stacks, Luc has led teams
                        and shipped across wildly different domains. He brings a rare combination of hardware-level
                        thinking and modern web development expertise.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        At NorthOps, Luc focuses on frontend architecture, TypeScript, and AI integrations —
                        building the interfaces and intelligent features that users interact with. Based in
                        Noelville, Ontario.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Principles -->
    <section class="section">
        <div class="container container-narrow">
            <h2>Principles</h2>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li>Senior engineers on every project — no juniors, no exceptions.</li>
                <li>Fixed pricing with clear scope — you know the cost before we start.</li>
                <li>Ship in days, not weeks — because we've built these systems before.</li>
                <li>Direct communication — you talk to the people writing the code.</li>
                <li>Clean handoffs — documented, deployed, and ready for the next person.</li>
                <li>Honest about fit — if we're not the right team for your project, we'll say so.</li>
                <li>AI-augmented by default — modern tooling is part of how we work, not an upsell.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA Banner -->
    <section class="section section-cta">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Work with us.</h2>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Started</a>
        </div>
    </section>
{% endblock %}
